these assholes finish their goddam lunch!

600
00:37:49,785 --> 00:37:52,784
You got that? Hey you....

601
00:37:52,943 --> 00:37:55,782
There you go, you can't have a good
lunch without a nice piece of bread. Eat!

602
00:37:57,581 --> 00:37:58,980
Come on now, that's good.

603
00:37:59,700 --> 00:38:01,459
Show the boys how you follow my rules.

604
00:38:01,659 --> 00:38:03,858
Rules! You understand?

605
00:38:04,977 --> 00:38:07,536
Hey look, boys, see how
he follows my rules?

606
00:38:08,376 --> 00:38:09,375
Your shift's over, Nokes.

607
00:38:11,734 --> 00:38:13,933
I'm not ready to go yet.
I still got a few more things...

608
00:38:14,093 --> 00:38:16,132
...l gotta clean up here
before I can leave.

609
00:38:16,292 --> 00:38:19,210
It's my tour now.
I'll clean what needs cleaning.

610
00:38:19,370 --> 00:38:21,129
Stay out of this one. It's got
nothing to do with you.

611
00:38:21,889 --> 00:38:24,168
This one, I'm staying in.

612
00:38:28,486 --> 00:38:29,765
Don't fuck with me, boy.

613
00:38:31,724 --> 00:38:34,763
No, Nokes...you fuck with me.

614
00:38:36,362 --> 00:38:37,641
I'm asking you.

615
00:38:44,358 --> 00:38:45,757
You're eating into my shift.

616
00:38:48,756 --> 00:38:51,994
I'll get out of your way...for now.

617
00:38:53,193 --> 00:38:54,673
I'll take what I can get.

618
00:38:57,431 --> 00:38:58,711
You boys get off your knees.

619
00:39:11,984 --> 00:39:14,023
It's a tragedy. I'll tell you.

620
00:39:15,462 --> 00:39:17,741
I don't understand you boys.

621
00:39:17,781 --> 00:39:19,940
I don't think you know what
it means to have rules.

622
00:39:20,100 --> 00:39:22,179
You gotta have rules,
and you gotta have discipline.

623
00:39:22,938 --> 00:39:25,497
I don't know what it was like in your
homes and your home lives, but...

624
00:39:25,937 --> 00:39:29,135
...in my house with my father,
there were rules!

625
00:39:29,455 --> 00:39:32,374
And if you didn't follow the
rules, there was hell to pay.

626
00:39:33,093 --> 00:39:35,652
You had rules, and you had discipline.

627
00:39:37,211 --> 00:39:41,529
Sometimes, it wasn't nice, but
we learned. We sure did learn.

628
00:39:43,608 --> 00:39:46,167
Right around there to the right.
There you go.

629
00:39:52,404 --> 00:39:56,841
I mean, it's a simple thing, really.
You got rules, and you got discipline.

630
00:39:57,561 --> 00:40:00,120
That's the beginning of the story,
and that's the end of the story.

631
00:40:07,156 --> 00:40:08,236
We understand each other?

632
00:40:09,075 --> 00:40:10,155
Turn and face the wall.

633
00:40:19,190 --> 00:40:22,309
Now, we got interrupted earlier
in the lunch room, but...

634
00:40:23,348 --> 00:40:25,067
...there's no one
to interrupt us here now.

635
00:40:35,462 --> 00:40:36,342
What do you want?

636
00:40:38,541 --> 00:40:39,820
A blow job.

637
00:40:47,936 --> 00:40:48,895
Down on your knees.

638
00:40:52,654 --> 00:40:54,573
Face the wall.

639
00:41:10,685 --> 00:41:13,523
There are no clear pictures of
the sexual abuse we endured.

640
00:41:14,043 --> 00:41:16,122
I buried it as deep as
it could possibly go.

641
00:41:17,201 --> 00:41:19,720
What I remember most clearly
from that chilly October night...

642
00:41:19,800 --> 00:41:21,239
...was that it was
my fourteenth birthday...

643
00:41:22,079 --> 00:41:23,638
...and the end of my childhood.

644
00:41:33,393 --> 00:41:36,272
Early in my stay, I'd written and
asked my father not to come.

645
00:41:37,071 --> 00:41:39,310
I couldn't look at my father
and have him see on my face...

646
00:41:39,470 --> 00:41:40,390
...all that had happened to me.

647
00:41:41,069 --> 00:41:43,788
Michael had done the same with the
interested members of his family.

648
00:41:43,948 --> 00:41:45,867
Tommy's mother couldn't get
it together to visit.

649
00:41:46,147 --> 00:41:47,946
John's mother came up once a month.

650
00:41:52,144 --> 00:41:53,783
But no one could stop Father
Bobby from visiting.

651
00:41:55,942 --> 00:41:58,820
So listen, let's try to keep
this on a happy note, okay?

652
00:41:59,500 --> 00:42:01,939
Nokes warned us not to say
anything to Father Bobby.

653
00:42:02,539 --> 00:42:05,097
If we did, reprisals would be severe.

654
00:42:19,330 --> 00:42:20,809
You lost a few pounds.

655
00:42:21,569 --> 00:42:23,048
It's not exactly home cooking.

656
00:42:24,648 --> 00:42:25,607
Sit down.

657
00:42:26,966 --> 00:42:28,646
This is where I get to see
all four of you guys today.

658
00:42:30,005 --> 00:42:32,644
I loved Father Bobby, but I
couldn't stand to look at him.

659
00:42:33,923 --> 00:42:35,162
I was afraid he'd look
right through me...

660
00:42:35,242 --> 00:42:36,921
...past the fear and shame,
right through to the truth.

661
00:42:37,281 --> 00:42:40,160
Shakes, is there anything
you want to tell me?

662
00:42:42,199 --> 00:42:43,318
Anything at all?

663
00:42:45,597 --> 00:42:46,916
You shouldn't come here anymore, Father.

664
00:42:49,555 --> 00:42:51,114
I appreciate it and all, but...

665
00:42:52,154 --> 00:42:53,873
...l don't think it's the
right thing for you to do.

666
00:43:17,861 --> 00:43:20,939
I stopped off at Attica today on my
way up here to see an old friend.

667
00:43:22,339 --> 00:43:23,738
You have any friends not in jail?

668
00:43:25,937 --> 00:43:27,136
Not as many as I would like.

669
00:43:28,616 --> 00:43:29,855
What's he in for?

670
00:43:31,454 --> 00:43:35,052
Triple murder. He killed three
men about fifteen years ago.

671
00:43:36,492 --> 00:43:37,411
And he's a good friend?

672
00:43:38,331 --> 00:43:39,130
He's my best friend.

673
00:43:42,009 --> 00:43:43,008
We hung out together.

674
00:43:43,688 --> 00:43:45,927
We were close...
just like you and the guys.

675
00:43:57,801 --> 00:43:59,160
We were both sent up here.

676
00:44:02,758 --> 00:44:07,236
That's right. And it wasn't easy...

677
00:44:09,035 --> 00:44:11,154
...just like it's not easy
for you and the guys.

678
00:44:13,593 --> 00:44:17,031
This place killed him...
made him not care anymore.

679
00:44:21,549 --> 00:44:23,868
Don't let this place do
that to you, Shakes.

680
00:44:24,947 --> 00:44:27,146
Don't let it make you think
you're tougher than you are.

681
00:44:28,106 --> 00:44:30,025
I've got to go, Father.

682
00:44:38,221 --> 00:44:39,300
I'll see you in the Kitchen.

683
00:44:41,539 --> 00:44:42,539
I'm counting on you.

684
00:44:44,937 --> 00:44:46,976
Wipe the tears off your face.
Don't let them see it.

685
00:44:48,136 --> 00:44:51,654
Don't let them see you crying.
Don't give them the satisfaction.

686
00:44:54,852 --> 00:44:56,252
You'll be out of here
before you know it.

687
00:45:00,010 --> 00:45:01,129
You're gonna be okay.

688
00:45:07,926 --> 00:45:09,845
I didn't want to let him go.

689
00:45:10,205 --> 00:45:12,604
I never felt as close to anyone
as I felt to him at that moment.

690
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:22,359
A number of the inmates, as tough as
they acted during the day...

691
00:45:22,519 --> 00:45:24,318
...would often cry themselves
to sleep at night.

692
00:45:25,437 --> 00:45:26,716
There were other cries, too.

693
00:45:27,516 --> 00:45:29,715
These differed from those
filled with fear and loneliness.

694
00:45:30,395 --> 00:45:33,833
They were lower and muffled;
the sounds of pained anguish.

695
00:45:35,152 --> 00:45:37,471
Those cries can change
the course of a life.

696
00:45:38,111 --> 00:45:40,949
They are cries that, once heard,
can never be erased from memory.

697
00:45:41,429 --> 00:45:44,148
On this one night, those cries
belonged to my friend, John...

698
00:45:44,588 --> 00:45:46,467
...when Ralph Ferguson
paid him a visit.

699
00:46:02,698 --> 00:46:05,257
I was expecting to read 30
book reports over the weekend.

700
00:46:05,617 --> 00:46:08,975
There are only 6 for me to read...
which means I'm missing how many?

701
00:46:10,575 --> 00:46:13,613
This is English class.
Math is down the hall.

702
00:46:17,411 --> 00:46:20,170
I want to help you.
You may not believe that.

703
00:46:20,809 --> 00:46:22,249
Or you may not care, but it's the truth.

704
00:46:29,845 --> 00:46:32,404
-You got a second?
-What, I do something wrong?

705
00:46:32,963 --> 00:46:35,282
No. You did a great
job on your book report.

706
00:46:37,521 --> 00:46:40,160
You really seemed to like the book,
"The Count of Monte Cristo."

707
00:46:40,320 --> 00:46:43,518
It's my favorite.
I like it more since I've been here.

708
00:46:44,278 --> 00:46:44,877
Why is that?

709
00:46:46,397 --> 00:46:49,875
It's like...he wouldn't let
anyone beat him, the Count.

710
00:46:50,195 --> 00:46:54,353
Took what he had to take,
beatings, insults and whatever.

711
00:46:55,352 --> 00:46:56,312
And he learned from it.

712
00:46:57,551 --> 00:47:00,629
Then when the time came for him to
do something, he made his move.

713
00:47:02,229 --> 00:47:04,907
-You admire that?
-No, I respect that.

714
00:47:06,706 --> 00:47:08,466
You got a copy of the book at home?

715
00:47:09,265 --> 00:47:10,864
I got the Classics Illustrated Comic.

716
00:47:11,864 --> 00:47:13,103
No, it's not the same thing.

717
00:47:13,863 --> 00:47:15,982
Listen, I gotta go.
I'm gonna miss morning roll call.

718
00:47:16,262 --> 00:47:18,700
I've got something for you.

719
00:47:20,540 --> 00:47:21,779
I thought you might like to have it.

720
00:47:22,738 --> 00:47:23,658
Are you serious?

721
00:47:24,098 --> 00:47:26,537
Well, you love the book that much.
You should have a copy of your own.

722
00:47:27,136 --> 00:47:29,495
-I can't pay you.
-It's a gift.

723
00:47:30,614 --> 00:47:31,894
You've gotten gifts before,
haven't you?

724
00:47:32,054 --> 00:47:33,093
It's been a while.

725
00:47:34,253 --> 00:47:37,451
-Well, it's my way of saying, thanks.
-For what?

726
00:47:38,570 --> 00:47:41,129
That somebody listens...
even if it's just one student.

727
00:47:41,969 --> 00:47:43,288
You're a good teacher, Mr. Carlson.

728
00:47:43,368 --> 00:47:45,487
Listen, we can discuss the book
on Friday in class if you...

729
00:47:45,887 --> 00:47:47,326
...think the Count can
hold their attention.

730
00:47:47,646 --> 00:47:48,765
He's got a shot.

731
00:47:49,565 --> 00:47:50,804
Any particular section
I should read from?

732
00:47:51,524 --> 00:47:54,083
That's easy...the part where
he escapes from prison.

733
00:48:07,196 --> 00:48:09,915
There you go, All Star.
Here's your locker room!

734
00:48:17,151 --> 00:48:21,469
It was only a game...just a touch
football game, nothing more.

735
00:48:22,269 --> 00:48:23,948
But a game I wish we
had never played.

736
00:48:24,947 --> 00:48:28,625
Guards against inmates.
The guards practiced four times a week.

737
00:48:29,425 --> 00:48:31,504
Our team was picked the
Monday before the game.

738
00:48:32,184 --> 00:48:33,623
We had a 2 hour practice.

739
00:48:34,503 --> 00:48:35,662
It didn't matter much.

740
00:48:36,022 --> 00:48:38,900
We weren't supposed to win.
We were just supposed to show up.

741
00:48:39,540 --> 00:48:40,939
Who's the toughest guy here?

742
00:48:41,899 --> 00:48:43,058
How do you mean, tough?

743
00:48:43,538 --> 00:48:45,137
Who can talk and have
everyone listening?

744
00:48:45,297 --> 00:48:47,216
Rizzo. Black kid over there.

745
00:48:49,095 --> 00:48:52,454
Michael saw an opening...a chance
to bring the game to our level.

746
00:48:52,613 --> 00:48:56,452
Even out the field. But he needed help.
He needed Rizzo.

747
00:48:57,251 --> 00:49:01,169
Black kid with an Italian name.
With him on our side, we had a chance.

748
00:49:02,049 --> 00:49:04,927
Look, white boy, I don't know
what you play in the streets.

749
00:49:05,087 --> 00:49:07,246
I don't care. But in here,
the guards call the play...

750
00:49:07,406 --> 00:49:08,965
...and the play calls for
them to win the game.

751
00:49:09,045 --> 00:49:09,765
Why?

752
00:49:10,085 --> 00:49:11,044
Look man...

753
00:49:11,524 --> 00:49:12,963
...guards stay clear of me, all right?

754
00:49:13,123 --> 00:49:14,562
They stay back and let me do my time.

755
00:49:14,882 --> 00:49:16,641
If I play that game and I
put a hurt on one of them...

756
00:49:16,801 --> 00:49:18,361
...they just might change my cushion.

757
00:49:18,560 --> 00:49:21,599
I'm not saying we gotta win.
I just don't want to take a beating.

758
00:49:22,119 --> 00:49:23,038
You do every day.

759
00:49:23,718 --> 00:49:26,876
-Why is Saturday special?
-'Cause on Saturday, we can hit back.

760
00:49:29,915 --> 00:49:32,833
They don't fuck with you like they do us,
but they fuck with you another way!

761
00:49:32,993 --> 00:49:34,193
You're just an animal to them.

762
00:49:35,312 --> 00:49:37,871
-I don't give a fuck!
-Yeah, you do.

763
00:49:38,231 --> 00:49:40,629
And beating them on Saturday
is not gonna change a thing.

764
00:49:41,469 --> 00:49:42,588
Then why, white boy, why?

765
00:49:42,748 --> 00:49:46,946
To make them feel what we feel
...just for a couple of hours.

766
00:49:49,065 --> 00:49:50,784
Now, don't try anything funny, Sambo.

767
00:49:50,984 --> 00:49:53,023
Nobody will get hurt.
You know what I'm saying?

768
00:49:53,423 --> 00:49:54,303
I call heads.

769
00:49:57,301 --> 00:49:59,220
He called heads.
It is a head.

770
00:50:01,099 --> 00:50:01,979
Let's go.

771
00:50:11,814 --> 00:50:15,012
You're gonna die, mother fucker!
You're gonna fucking die!

772
00:50:25,287 --> 00:50:27,206
None of you motherfuckers can cover me!

773
00:50:27,526 --> 00:50:30,724
We got ourselves a game!
I'm feeling good today.

774
00:50:31,204 --> 00:50:32,324
This shit feels good.

775
00:50:39,080 --> 00:50:40,000
Fuck!

776
00:50:46,157 --> 00:50:48,076
Get the fuck off me!

777
00:50:58,910 --> 00:51:01,589
Yeah, keep smiling, you little piss ant.

778
00:51:04,468 --> 00:51:07,026
For 90 minutes, we took
the game out of the prison...

779
00:51:07,626 --> 00:51:09,465
...moved it miles beyond
the locked gates...

780
00:51:09,625 --> 00:51:11,664
...and the sloping hills of
the surrounding countryside...

781
00:51:12,264 --> 00:51:14,942
...and brought it back down to the streets
of the neighborhoods we'd come from.

782
00:51:16,142 --> 00:51:18,860
For those 90 minutes,
we were once again free!

783
00:51:36,931 --> 00:51:38,371
Rizzo! Rizzo!

784
00:51:49,805 --> 00:51:53,443
Rizzo...Rizzo.

785
00:51:55,082 --> 00:51:58,121
Hey, Nokes.
Good game.

786
00:52:00,919 --> 00:52:04,118
For once, we had a victory.
But it didn't last.

787
00:52:04,757 --> 00:52:08,915
It couldn't last...
and all I wanted to do was die.

788
00:52:09,955 --> 00:52:13,793
I was not alone in the hole. I knew my
friends were down in the depths with me.

789
00:52:14,313 --> 00:52:18,430
Each in his own cell, each in his own
pain...suffering his own demons.

790
00:52:19,030 --> 00:52:20,110
Rizzo was there, too.

791
00:52:23,028 --> 00:52:24,627
I had lost any sense of time.

792
00:53:03,808 --> 00:53:04,927
I thought you'd never wake up.

793
00:53:06,207 --> 00:53:07,486
I thought I'd never want to.

794
00:53:07,846 --> 00:53:10,884
John and Tommy, they're
on the other side there.

795
00:53:12,364 --> 00:53:15,882
How are they?
They're alive.

796
00:53:17,601 --> 00:53:18,560
Who isn't?

797
00:53:20,439 --> 00:53:21,359
Rizzo.

798
00:53:23,958 --> 00:53:25,077
They killed him?

799
00:53:26,996 --> 00:53:31,034
They took turns beating him until
there was nothing of that kid to beat.

800
00:53:35,752 --> 00:53:37,111
Rizzo was dead because of us.

801
00:53:38,470 --> 00:53:40,390
We made him think that going
up against the guards...

802
00:53:40,469 --> 00:53:41,829
...in a meaningless football game...

803
00:53:41,989 --> 00:53:45,427
...had some value...that it would
give us a reason to go on.

804
00:53:46,546 --> 00:53:48,186
Once again, we were wrong.

805
00:53:51,224 --> 00:53:52,503
Did they give you
your release date yet?

806
00:53:52,663 --> 00:53:53,943
Nokes had a letter from the warden.

807
00:53:54,742 --> 00:53:56,541
Waved it in front of me,
then tore it up....

808
00:53:57,661 --> 00:53:58,460
When do you figure?

809
00:54:00,180 --> 00:54:02,299
End of spring, early
summer or something.

810
00:54:03,338 --> 00:54:04,817
I wish we were coming with you.

811
00:54:05,817 --> 00:54:08,056
It would've been nice for all
of us to walk out together.

812
00:54:09,295 --> 00:54:12,493
No use thinking about that. We're
gonna do a full year, not an hour less.

813
00:54:14,452 --> 00:54:17,651
When I get out, I could get Father
Bobby to make a couple of phone calls.

814
00:54:17,851 --> 00:54:19,210
Shave a month or two off.

815
00:54:19,370 --> 00:54:21,929
-There's nothing to talk about!
-There's a lot to talk about.

816
00:54:22,408 --> 00:54:25,207
Maybe, if people knew what was going
on in here, they'd make a move.

817
00:54:25,767 --> 00:54:27,366
I don't want anybody to know.

818
00:54:28,126 --> 00:54:31,684
Not Father Bobby, King Benny,
Fat Mancho...

819
00:54:31,844 --> 00:54:34,083
...not my mother. Nobody.

820
00:54:35,642 --> 00:54:37,121
I don't either.

821
00:54:37,201 --> 00:54:39,360
I mean, I wouldn't know what
to say to anyone who did know.

822
00:54:40,040 --> 00:54:42,598
I can't think of anybody
who needs to hear about it.

823
00:54:43,718 --> 00:54:46,157
Either they won't believe it,
or they won't give a shit.

824
00:54:47,076 --> 00:54:49,275
Yeah, I don't even think we should
talk about it once it's over.

825
00:54:51,514 --> 00:54:55,352
We got no choice but to live with it.
And talking makes living it harder.

826
00:54:56,671 --> 00:54:58,750
So, we might as well
not even talk about it.

827
00:54:59,710 --> 00:55:00,989
The truth stays with us.

828
00:55:04,028 --> 00:55:05,787
I want to be able to sleep one night...

829
00:55:07,266 --> 00:55:10,704
...and not have to worry who's coming
in my room, what's gonna happen to me.

830
00:55:14,303 --> 00:55:18,101
If I can get that, then I'll be happy.

831
00:55:20,659 --> 00:55:23,338
Someday, John, I promise.

832
00:55:39,330 --> 00:55:42,688
I was in my last hours as an inmate
at the Wilkinson Home for boys.

833
00:55:43,488 --> 00:55:45,327
I was given four copies
of my release form.

834
00:55:45,687 --> 00:55:47,886
The final reminder of my
time at Wilkinson.

835
00:55:50,245 --> 00:55:51,764
I never heard the key
turn in the lock...

836
00:55:52,324 --> 00:55:54,322
...and I never heard
the snap of the bolt.

837
00:55:55,762 --> 00:55:57,041
You should be asleep.

838
00:55:58,241 --> 00:56:02,119
I just wanted to say goodbye.
We all do.

839
00:56:04,997 --> 00:56:06,916
I told him. I told him right
to his face. I said,

840
00:56:07,076 --> 00:56:08,835
I don't care if you're paying me
overtime or not.

841
00:56:08,915 --> 00:56:10,394
I'm not working those kind of hours.

842
00:56:10,594 --> 00:56:11,874
Yeah, did you put in for it?

843
00:56:12,353 --> 00:56:13,273
I put in for it!

844
00:56:13,313 --> 00:56:14,952
Because I put in for it.
They don't give it to me.

845
00:56:15,552 --> 00:56:18,630
I come in early for three days.
Do they give me overtime? No!

846
00:56:19,750 --> 00:56:21,629
A part of all of us was
left there that night.

847
00:56:22,628 --> 00:56:24,867
That night will never be
removed from my mind.

848
00:56:25,427 --> 00:56:29,785
The night of June 1, 1968--
the Summer of Love.

849
00:56:31,384 --> 00:56:33,303
My last night at the
Wilkinson Home for boys.

850
00:57:18,161 --> 00:57:20,719
At 8:25 p.m. two men
walked through the doors.

851
00:57:21,679 --> 00:57:24,637
The bartender knew their faces as most
of the neighborhood knew their names.

852
00:57:25,037 --> 00:57:27,556
They were two of the founding
members of the West Side Boys.

853
00:57:27,636 --> 00:57:29,075
They were also its deadliest.

854
00:57:31,074 --> 00:57:33,953
The blond-haired man had been in and out
of jail since he was a teenager.

855
00:57:34,512 --> 00:57:36,511
He robbed and killed
at will or on command.

856
00:57:37,311 --> 00:57:39,870
He was presently a suspect in
four unsolved homicides.

857
00:57:40,429 --> 00:57:43,868
He was an alcoholic and a cocaine abuser
with a fast temper and a faster trigger.

858
00:57:44,307 --> 00:57:47,026
He once shot a mechanic dead for
moving ahead of him in a movie line.

859
00:57:49,225 --> 00:57:51,144
The dark-haired man was equally deadly...

860
00:57:51,184 --> 00:57:53,383
...and had committed his
first murder at the age of 17.

861
00:57:54,223 --> 00:57:57,901
In return, he was paid $50.
He drank, and he did drugs...

862
00:57:58,061 --> 00:58:01,059
...and he had a wife he never saw,
living somewhere in Queens.

863
00:58:03,658 --> 00:58:06,936
He's making a noble attempt
to really change things.

864
00:58:07,016 --> 00:58:10,534
-The Republicans will take the House.
-Well, we got a lot of work to do.

865
00:58:10,654 --> 00:58:12,254
It's gonna take more
than 4 years to get....

866
00:58:12,413 --> 00:58:13,573
They'll take it at
the mid-term elections.

867
00:58:14,053 --> 00:58:16,771
He's got the charisma.
He's gonna do it.

868
00:58:16,971 --> 00:58:19,530
He's our man. Reagan's
the man who's gonna do it.

869
00:58:21,089 --> 00:58:23,208
Hey, Jerry...
What are they talking about?

870
00:58:23,608 --> 00:58:25,527
They're talking about Reagan's speech.

871
00:58:28,405 --> 00:58:30,804
Order those two men some
drinks and put it on my tab.

872
00:58:32,643 --> 00:58:35,362
You tell them that Republicans
are not welcome in Hell's Kitchen...

873
00:58:35,522 --> 00:58:38,880
...and either a political conversion or
a change of conversation is in order.

874
00:58:39,280 --> 00:58:40,240
Sure thing.

875
00:58:46,996 --> 00:58:49,795
The gentlemen there would like to
buy you a drink on one condition.

876
00:58:50,075 --> 00:58:53,633
You know the rules:
no religion, no politics.

877
00:58:54,232 --> 00:58:55,312
You get my meaning?

878
00:59:12,463 --> 00:59:14,662
Order something for me.
I gotta go to the bathroom.

879
00:59:44,247 --> 00:59:45,327
Can I help you with something, chief?

880
00:59:47,126 --> 00:59:51,324
Not right now.
Enjoy the rest of your meal.

881
01:00:35,502 --> 01:00:39,540
I ordered brisket on a roll,
with fries and...

882
01:00:40,899 --> 01:00:43,538
...two baskets of soda bread.
I know how you like that shit.

883
01:00:44,617 --> 01:00:45,577
Is that okay by you?

884
01:00:47,856 --> 01:00:50,814
Take a look at the guy at the table.
Take a good look.

885
01:01:02,168 --> 01:01:03,208
Motherfucker.

886
01:01:28,635 --> 01:01:30,154
That's him.

887
01:01:30,434 --> 01:01:31,794
Are you fucking kidding me?

888
01:01:35,192 --> 01:01:35,872
Bingo!

889
01:02:00,539 --> 01:02:01,619
This is amazing.

890
01:02:01,779 --> 01:02:04,337
Hello...it's been a long time!

891
01:02:06,017 --> 01:02:07,056
Who the fuck are you guys?

892
01:02:11,254 --> 01:02:12,773
Who the fuck asked you to sit down?

893
01:02:13,253 --> 01:02:16,211
I thought you'd be happy to see us.
I guess I was wrong.

894
01:02:17,971 --> 01:02:20,289
You know, I thought
you'd do a lot better.

895
01:02:20,929 --> 01:02:23,048
You know, with all that training...
all that time you put in...

896
01:02:23,648 --> 01:02:25,607
...just to end up watching
someone else's money.

897
01:02:25,927 --> 01:02:27,166
That seems like a waste.

898
01:02:27,366 --> 01:02:29,245
I'm asking you now for the last
time, what the fuck do you want?

899
01:02:29,445 --> 01:02:31,084
Why don't you take your time?
It'll come to you.

900
01:02:36,641 --> 01:02:38,360
I can see how he might forget us.

901
01:02:39,000 --> 01:02:41,799
You know, we were just something for
you and your friends to play with.

902
01:02:41,959 --> 01:02:43,998
It's a little harder for us to forget.

903
01:02:44,357 --> 01:02:46,516
You gave us so much more to remember.

904
01:02:49,755 --> 01:02:51,074
You can't quite place us,
can you, chief?

905
01:02:51,794 --> 01:02:55,632
Let me help you out. You're looking
at John Reilly and Tommy Marcano.

906
01:03:06,626 --> 01:03:07,506
Yeah, that's right.

907
01:03:14,023 --> 01:03:15,302
That was a long time ago.

908
01:03:18,700 --> 01:03:19,420
So how you been?

909
01:03:20,379 --> 01:03:21,819
Yeah, we ain't kids now.

910
01:03:23,058 --> 01:03:24,337
So, what do you want?

911
01:03:25,137 --> 01:03:28,335
What I've always wanted
is to watch you die!

912
01:03:34,132 --> 01:03:35,132
You ordered the meat loaf.

913
01:03:36,691 --> 01:03:39,570
The brisket's really good here,
only you'll never know it.

914
01:03:40,809 --> 01:03:41,609
You fucked up.

915
01:03:54,842 --> 01:03:59,000
Yeah, you were scared little pricks,
both of you.

916
01:04:00,479 --> 01:04:04,957
All of you...scared shitless.
But l...

917
01:04:06,796 --> 01:04:10,114
...l tried to make you tough.
I tried to make you hard.

918
01:04:10,154 --> 01:04:13,633
I had you all wrong then, Nokes.
All this time I thought you just liked...

919
01:04:13,793 --> 01:04:15,232
...fucking and beating up little boys.

920
01:04:15,432 --> 01:04:17,591
You two motherfuckers
are gonna burn in hell!

921
01:04:18,150 --> 01:04:19,430
You're gonna burn in hell.

922
01:04:19,590 --> 01:04:20,509
Yeah, after you.

923
01:04:26,066 --> 01:04:27,186
Did that hurt, Nokes?

924
01:05:03,168 --> 01:05:07,246
Jerry, sorry, should've made
those brisket sandwiches to go.

925
01:05:19,320 --> 01:05:20,599
John Reilly, how do you plead?

926
01:05:20,959 --> 01:05:22,078
Not guilty, Your Honor.

927
01:05:22,998 --> 01:05:23,838
Thomas Marcano?

928
01:05:25,277 --> 01:05:26,396
Not guilty, Your Honor.

929
01:05:26,916 --> 01:05:30,474
John Reilly and Thomas Marcano,
you are hereby held without bail.

930
01:05:31,634 --> 01:05:34,912
In all the years since Wilkinson's, we
had never once spoken to each other...

931
01:05:35,072 --> 01:05:38,270
...about what happened there.
We remained caring friends...

932
01:05:38,430 --> 01:05:40,349
...but the relationship
had been altered.

933
01:05:41,469 --> 01:05:45,467
We drifted together, always wondering
if that moment would arrive...

934
01:05:45,907 --> 01:05:47,586
...that would force us to
deal with the past.

935
01:06:00,539 --> 01:06:03,738
One down, Shakes, one down.

936
01:06:05,657 --> 01:06:06,456
One what?

937
01:06:08,615 --> 01:06:11,814
One Sean Nokes.

938
01:06:12,933 --> 01:06:13,773
Nokes?

939
01:06:21,729 --> 01:06:22,928
At the time of Nokes' shooting,

940
01:06:22,968 --> 01:06:25,807
Michael was working as an
Assistant New York District Attorney.

941
01:06:26,566 --> 01:06:29,205
I got a call that he wanted to meet me
on 45th Street in Queens.

942
01:06:30,004 --> 01:06:30,924
Then, he hung up.

943
01:06:35,282 --> 01:06:36,921
-So, what did they say?
-What?

944
01:06:37,161 --> 01:06:38,360
John and Tommy, what'd they say?

945
01:06:38,520 --> 01:06:39,800
It's a little cloak and
dagger, isn't it, Mike?

946
01:06:40,679 --> 01:06:42,598
Nokes?
Did they talk about him?

947
01:06:44,437 --> 01:06:45,717
-John did.
-Yeah?

948
01:06:46,556 --> 01:06:47,516
What did he say?

949
01:06:48,315 --> 01:06:50,834
He said, "One down, Shakes.
One down."

950
01:06:54,232 --> 01:06:56,151
I hear they hired Danny Snyder
as the lawyer, is that right?

951
01:06:56,311 --> 01:06:58,710
It's temporary. King Benny's
gonna move in one of his lawyers.

952
01:06:58,950 --> 01:07:01,509
Don't let him do that.
Snyder's perfect.

953
01:07:01,749 --> 01:07:04,027
-Perfect? The guy's a fall down drunk!
-Then he is perfect.

954
01:07:04,507 --> 01:07:05,587
Perfect for what?

955
01:07:09,465 --> 01:07:11,224
Are you covering this
story for your newspaper?

956
01:07:11,384 --> 01:07:12,343
-Me?
-Yeah.

957
01:07:12,663 --> 01:07:16,181
I'm a timetable clerk, Mikey. Ask me
what movie's playing at what time.

958
01:07:16,341 --> 01:07:17,261
I'm lucky they let me in the building.

959
01:07:22,098 --> 01:07:22,898
Get some coffee?

960
01:07:23,898 --> 01:07:24,817
Let's take a walk.

961
01:07:35,372 --> 01:07:37,131
I'm gonna prosecute John
and Tommy in an open court.

962
01:07:38,490 --> 01:07:39,890
What, are you fucking nuts?

963
01:07:41,049 --> 01:07:41,689
Just hear me out.

964
01:07:42,048 --> 01:07:44,727
You should stay home tomorrow.
Call in sick and save your life, counsel.

965
01:07:44,887 --> 01:07:46,166
I'm not taking this case to win.

966
01:07:47,646 --> 01:07:49,245
I'm taking this case to lose.

967
01:07:50,604 --> 01:07:51,404
What does that mean?

968
01:07:53,723 --> 01:07:55,242
It means it's payback time.

969
01:07:56,321 --> 01:08:00,559
Look, John and Tommy started this.
It's begun.

970
01:08:01,279 --> 01:08:04,517
It's messy, it's not how I had
it planned but...here it is.

971
01:08:05,917 --> 01:08:08,475
And you and l, we can finish it.

972
01:08:09,315 --> 01:08:10,514
Finish what, Mikey?

973
01:08:12,793 --> 01:08:14,552
You read "The Count of
Monte Cristo" lately?

974
01:08:16,311 --> 01:08:18,310
I don't know...ten years ago.

975
01:08:19,430 --> 01:08:21,669
You see, I read a little
bit of it every night.

976
01:08:22,748 --> 01:08:26,786
I read words like 'revenge'.
Sweet, lasting revenge.

977
01:08:28,865 --> 01:08:30,344
Payback time.

978
01:08:32,103 --> 01:08:33,383
It's our time.

979
01:08:34,142 --> 01:08:35,342
What are you saying, Mike?

980
01:08:36,261 --> 01:08:38,940
I'm saying it's time for
all of us to get a taste.

981
01:08:40,659 --> 01:08:42,578
I'm saying it's time
to put an end to this.

982
01:08:44,657 --> 01:08:45,657
Let's walk.

983
01:08:49,375 --> 01:08:50,774
So, I asked for the case.

984
01:08:50,854 --> 01:08:52,733
I told them I was from the same
neighborhood as the accused...

985
01:08:52,893 --> 01:08:54,812
...knew the mentality of the area,
blah, blah, blah...

986
01:08:55,092 --> 01:08:55,932
They bought it.

987
01:08:56,771 --> 01:08:58,770
And the connection between
John, Tommy and Nokes?

988
01:08:59,250 --> 01:09:01,928
What connection? All juvenile records
are destroyed after seven years.

989
01:09:02,848 --> 01:09:04,447
We were never at Wilkinson's.

